tip.text: Unajyu here is very delicious. My only prob is the rice texture. It's not like distinct pearls but rather mushy lumps. Sashimi slices are very thick but thick does not equate good. Good value though.
Amazing amai ebi and fresh sashimi. The ebi is so creamy, it's ridiculous. Price is on the higher side but service can be improved.
Never eat the soon lee char kuey teow. I got 4$ and there were 2 prawns and no cockles whatsoever. Hoho delicacies is something u shld look out for. Peanut sesame ball is amazing!
Chappati, dahl and keema is so good. Also thosai in the morning. Yummmm
Service could be more attentive. Exp: don't walk away whilst we're ordering or don't serve people food whilst holding empty dishes that you're clearing. Other than that had the ragu and it was good.

venue.name: Yong He Soy Milk King (永和豆漿大王)

tip.text: Bread is really impressive. Atmosphere is a bit too noisy. I personally wish that they wouldn't play the radio and would rather play instrumental that would suit the relaxed and chill environment.
Penang laksa tastes alright but seems like something is missing. Caesar salad isn't even a Caesar salad. It's served with no croutons and with thousand island sauce. COME ON.
I'm a fan of the hitsumabushi but the problem is it's not always consistent in taste. Their tako wasabi is the best I've tasted so far. My sister always orders negitoro-don and it's great!
Quiet in the morning but can get really noisy when there are more ppl. Drinks are the usual prices ranging from 3.50 for espresso to 8 for baileys coffee. Service is ok.
Service could be better. Had the chunky steak pie stack set. Only 7$ and tasted good. Clean and quiet environment even on a Sunday.
